Shorthand has been around for a long time. One of the first systems recorded [was developed by Marcus Tullius Tiro](https://web.archive.org/web/20160708114901/http://faculty.ithaca.edu/direnzo/docs/scholarship/mastersvoice.pdf), a slave of Cicero, in the first century BC. Tironian shorthand was used by scribes in the Roman Empire and later adapted by European monasteries in the medieval period.

