In 2021 [ownership of the system was transferred to the NCTJ](https://www.nctj.com/news/the-nctj-becomes-the-new-home-of-teeline-shorthand/), which brought it out of copyright for the public benefit to support journalism training and standards.

Shorthand has become a more optional part of journalism training in recent years, but it is still widely used in the industry and beyond. You should totally learn it.